Manchester City striker, Sergio Aguero, has admitted it will be “too hard” for his side to catch up with Premier League leaders, Liverpool. Sergio stated this while speaking to Sky sports, after he netted in City’s 2-0 win over Sheffield United at the Etihad. The victory sees the champions remain 14 points behind Liverpool, who have a game in hand. City, however, currently sit in third place, one point behind second-placed Leicester. “Now, Liverpool is too hard. We have to focus just on winning because we need to play Champions League next season. “We have to play the same way and see what happens,” Aguero said. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.